      <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
         <head altrender="organization" id="a2">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
         <p>1% for Peace was founded in Ithaca (N.Y.) with direct assistance from Ben and Jerry's
            Ice Cream to promote the direction of 1% of the Defense Dept. budget to social causes.
            In January 1992, the group changed its name to Business Partnership for Peace and
            clarified its mission as a lobbying group for an alternative approach to national
            security issues. In 1993 the group officially merged with Businesses for Social
            Responsibility and moved its operations to Washington, DC.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
         <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
         <p>Correspondence, records, subject files, financial and organizational records, records
            pertaining to the founding of 1% for Peace, letters received and queries, and
            ephemera.</p>
      </scopecontent>
